      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:43:33",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ لَا تَضْطَجِعْ فِي الْحَمَّامِ فَإِنَّهُ يُذِيبُ شَحْمَ الْكُلْيَتَيْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "One of our companions, from Ibn Jamhour, from Muhammad Bin Al Qasim, from Ibn Abu Yafour, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Do not lie down in the bathhouse, for it melts the fat of the kidneys’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "33. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘ Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is not harmful if one reads al-Quran in a bathhouse if he does it for the sake of Allah, but not to find out how his voice is.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
